ygData.messageBody:
In a message dated 6/12/99 4:30:02 AM Eastern Daylight Time,
markm@... writes:

> Not sure if this has come up here or not, but I spent the last 2 days
> *slaughtering* gnolls in Blackburrow. probably about 6-8 hrs of pure
> carnage. Mostly concentrating on the commanders/elite guards in the top
> rooms. After all this, I decided to check my faction, and I'm happy to say
> that I just successfully banked in the fair city of Qeynos. Those human
> types aren't so bad afterall...just have to clean up their vermin first :)

I do warn you to be carefull about the elves in the town.

I am also able to bank... but I decided to go to a nearby building to wait
for my group, and a High Elf merchant wandered INTO the building I was in and
killed me... (each hit for like 160 points of damage!!!) So don't be
overconfident in Qeynos.

Sonoroud Tomebinder
